The Chronicle Thupeyo Muleya, Beitbridge Bureau THIRTEEN Zimbabweans were on Monday afternoon killed when a Masmery bus they were travelling in overturned outside Makhado town in Limpopo province. The incident occurred along the N1 highway. However, details about the bus’s destination and the number of the injured are yet to be ascertained. Limpopo’s Member of Executive Committee responsible for Transport and Community Safety Makoma Makhurupetje said in a statement that the accident was devastating. More to follow…